comments.message:
I wonder if it would be better if we extract the anonymous embedded struct type definition for the tty member out to a named struct type, and then pass the pointer to that through here. It would still have all the same churn, but defines the API boundaries a bit more neatly? So:

```
struct console_tty {
    const char *name;
    ...
};

struct console_server {
    struct console_tty tty;
    ...
};
...
void tty_init_termios(struct console_tty *);
...
```

However, this is just a half-baked thought that needs discussion of its merit, let's not chase the implementation yet.
